}

<section class="content">
    <row>
        &emsp;
    </row>

    <row>
        <ol class="breadcrumb">
            <li><a href="@Url.Action("Index","STARHandbook")">STAR Handbook</a></li>
            <li><a href="@Url.Action("Scheduling","STARHandbook")">Scheduling</a></li>
            <li class="active">Editing a Schedule</li>
        </ol>
    </row>

    <row>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><strong>Editing a Schedule</strong></h4>
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>At times you may need to amend your schedules to ensure they are accurate, either in response to trends or changes in the business, or to accommodate your team.</p>
                <p>Changes can be made in any schedule period that has <strong>not</strong> been signed off, however you should not edit shift in the <i>current week</i> unless you need to add a cover shift. All other Ad-Hoc changes should be managed on the Timecard.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </row>

    @Html.Partial("~/Views/Partials/_ScheduleOptions.cshtml")

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
        </div>
    </div>
</section>